# Conventional PR titles (GitHub Actions)

PR titles are validated by `.github/workflows/pull-request-title.yml` against [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/). Allowed **scopes** are only:

- `deps`
- `deps-dev`
- `README`

Do **not** add new scopes to that workflow to “make a title pass.” If no allowed scope fits the change (for example work under `packages/core/` or `packages/plugin-sequelize/`), use a **scope-free** title instead, for example:

- `refactor: rename list pagination args to skip and limit`
- `feat: add association list wrapper`
- `fix: correct offset handling`
- `ci: adjust workflow condition`
- `docs: update plugin README`

Stacked branches opened with Graphite (`gt`) must follow the same rule when titling PRs.

# Graphite

When splitting or stacking work with Graphite, keep PR titles compliant without expanding the allowlist. Prefer `gt branch split` and small, focused branches; avoid drive-by edits to CI allowlists.
